body: It's intentional. It won't work good if onnxruntime use any submodules at build time.
Ok cool. I'll just do it manually.
BTW, seems you missed re2. re2 isn't in your list.

In the build dir, you may try this:
```
make onnxruntime
rm libonnxruntime.so
make VERBOSE=1 onnxruntime
```

Then the last step will show you all the libs needed.

So the following works for me:

```
create libonnxruntime_mono.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/libonnxruntime_common.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/libonnxruntime_framework.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/libonnxruntime_graph.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/libonnxruntime_mlas.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/libonnxruntime_optimizer.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/libonnxruntime_providers.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/libonnxruntime_session.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/libonnxruntime_test_utils.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/libonnxruntime_util.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/libonnx_test_data_proto.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/libonnx_test_runner_common.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/onnx/libonnx.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/onnx/libonnx_proto.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/lib/libgmock.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/lib/libgtest.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/external/nsync/libnsync_cpp.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/external/re2/libre2.a
addlib onnxruntime/build/Linux/Release/external/protobuf/cmake/libprotobuf-lite.a
save
end
```

body: @snnn @hariharans29 I think we should re-open the issue. There is an issue with op registration in the static build
Is there something to be done with the schema_registry when using the static build?

The problem is with ```Ort::Env```.
My program runs several models. If each session has its own ```Ort::Env``` it fails with error:
```
terminate called after throwing an instance of 'Ort::Exception'
  what():  Only one instance of LoggingManager created with InstanceType::Default can exist at any point in time.
```
So I thought i would use a global static instance:
```
static Ort::Env env;
```
then use that everywhere.
Now that works if using the dynamic library, i.e. libonnxruntime.so, but does not if you're using the static libraries.
To get around this I do the following:
```
Ort::Env& default_env()
{
    static Ort::Env INSTANCE(ORT_LOGGING_LEVEL_WARNING, "test");
    return INSTANCE;
}
```
and use default_env(). I guess the difference being that the singleton is created at runtime.

This repository is insanely good! It's so fast. And with an MRI script like the one above, it is a totally dependency free, single file static library (or shared library with no scripting). You guys should be really pushing for this to be the goto inference library. It's much better than OpenCV's DNN library or Tencent's NCNN, or feathercnn, or paddlepaddle, or anything else I've tried.
